# Backend (FastAPI)

Package: `backend/src/eventforge/`

## Structure

```
eventforge/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.py           # FastAPI app entry
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api/routes/       # HTTP endpoints
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api/deps.py       # Auth, DB session deps
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ agents/           # ingestion, embedding, knowledge, research, synthesis
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ workers/          # SQS long-poll consumers (one module per stage)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ events/           # publisher + Pydantic event schemas
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ db/models/        # SQLAlchemy 2.0 models
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ db/repositories/  # data access
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core/config.py    # pydantic-settings from .env
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core/otel.py      # OTEL spans
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ services/         # business logic
```

## Patterns

- Async everywhere (`async def`, `asyncpg`, `httpx`)
- Pydantic v2 for request/response + event payloads
- Config via `pydantic-settings` ‚Äî never hardcode secrets
- Structured JSON logs in prod; include `correlation_id`, `job_id`, `agent_name`
- OTEL span per agent step: `agent.{name}.{action}`

## API conventions

- Prefix: `/api/v1`
- Health: `GET /health`, `GET /health/ready` (checks DB, Qdrant, EB)
- SSE: `GET /api/v1/queries/{id}/stream` for pipeline updates

## Worker pattern

```python
# 1. Receive SQS message
# 2. Check processed_events(event_id) ‚Äî skip if exists
# 3. Process with OTEL span
# 4. Persist results (Postgres / Qdrant)
# 5. Publish next event to EventBridge
# 6. Delete message; on failure leave for retry ‚Üí DLQ
```

## DB models (MVP)

`User`, `Job`, `JobStage`, `ProcessedEvent`, `LLMUsage`, `Source`

